    "title": "Selecting an anchor for a Reality Composer scene"
  },
  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "Overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "Reality Composer",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text": " projects contain virtual scenes that you can add to real-world",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "environments using ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.RealityKit/documentation/RealityKit",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ". To place a ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "Reality Composer",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text": " scene into the real",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "world, you must anchor its content to a detected surface, image, face, or object.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.RealityKit/documentation/RealityKit",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " automatically detects appropriate anchors for many types of scenes,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "though you can also manually detect and place your scenes if you want more control",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "or have more specific anchoring requirements than ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "Reality Composer",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text": " provides.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "When you create a new project or add a scene to an existing project, Reality Composer",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "presents you with a sheet asking you to select an anchor type. The anchor type you",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "select defines how your scene’s content is added to the real world by identifying",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "the types of detected real-world surfaces, images, faces, or objects that you can",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "place it in relation to.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "You can manually load and anchor Reality Composer scenes using code, like",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": " ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "you do with other ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/ARKit",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "type": "reference"
                },
                {
                  "text": " content. When",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": " ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "you anchor a scene in code, RealityKit ignores the scene’s anchoring information.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Note",
          "style": "note",
          "type": "aside"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "Reality Composer",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text": " supports five anchor types: Horizontal, Vertical, Image, Face,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "and Object. It displays a different set of guides for each anchor type to help you",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "place your content. You can change the anchor type later if you choose the wrong",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "option or change your mind about how to anchor your scene.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "For each anchor type, ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "Reality Composer",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text": " automatically creates a default scene for",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "you. You can use the default scene as a placeholder to test your code until you are",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "ready to construct your own scene. If you do not want ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "Reality Composer",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text": " to add content",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "to your newly created scene, deselect the “Create with default content” checkbox",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "at the bottom left of the action sheet.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "identifier": "selecting-an-anchor-for-a-reality-composer-scene-1",
              "type": "image"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Select-horizontal-anchoring-for-tables-and-floors",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Select horizontal anchoring for tables and floors",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Horizontal anchoring is the default option when creating a new document or scene.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "Use this anchor type for scenes containing 3D objects to be placed on a table, floor,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "or other flat surface. When you select a horizontal anchor for your scene, Reality",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "Composer shows a guide grid to represent the real-world surface onto which it will",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "place your scene.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "identifier": "selecting-an-anchor-for-a-reality-composer-scene-2",
              "type": "image"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Select-vertical-anchoring-for-walls-and-free-floating-objects",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Select vertical anchoring for walls and free-floating objects",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Use vertical anchoring for scenes that contain objects to be placed against a wall,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "column, or other vertical surface. A vertical anchor is a good choice for scenes",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "that contain, for example, a shelf, a basketball hoop, or a wall clock. After you",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "select this anchor type, Reality Composer displays a vertical grid that represents",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "the wall or other detected vertical surface to position the scene against.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "identifier": "selecting-an-anchor-for-a-reality-composer-scene-3",
              "type": "image"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Select-image-anchoring-to-augment-real-world-2D-images",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Select image anchoring to augment real-world 2D images",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Select image anchoring to place your scene over or near an existing two-dimensional",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "image in the real world, such as a poster, painting, or photograph. After you select",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "this anchor type, ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "Reality Composer",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text": " displays a white-square guide to represent the",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "detected real-world image to place your content near. Any object in your scene that",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "is in front of the guide will appear in front of the detected image.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "In the Properties inspector, select a reference image asset that you want ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/ARKit",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "to detect. The white square then changes to the selected reference image, indicating",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "that ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/ARKit",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " will look for that specific",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "image and automatically anchor your scene to it. ARKit continues tracking the image’s",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "location so that if the image moves, your scene moves with it. In the scene, you",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "should also select the real-world size of the image you want ARKit to detect, by",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "using the Physical Height and Physical Width controls in the Scene inspector.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.RealityKit/documentation/RealityKit",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "type": "reference"
                },
                {
                  "text": "’s automatic anchoring and tracking will not work for",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": " ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "your scene if you do not select a reference image. However, you may wish to leave",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": " ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "the reference image empty for some scenes. If, for example, you wish to attach the",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": " ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "same scene to multiple reference images, you will need to configure ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/ARKit",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "type": "reference"
                },
                {
                  "text": "’s",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": " ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "image detection and then anchor your scene manually. For more information about configuring",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": " ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "image detection, see ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/ARKit/detecting-images-in-an-ar-experience",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "type": "reference"
                },
                {
                  "text": ".",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Important",
          "style": "important",
          "type": "aside"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "identifier": "selecting-an-anchor-for-a-reality-composer-scene-4",
              "type": "image"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Select-face-anchoring-to-place-a-scene-relative-to-a-detected-face",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Select face anchoring to place a scene relative to a detected face",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Select face anchoring to place content on or near detected human faces in ARKit.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "When you select this anchor type, ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "Reality Composer",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text": " displays a 3D face to stand",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "in for the real-world face that ARKit has detected. You can’t move or edit the face",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "guide, but the contents of your scene are placed into the real world based on their",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "relative position to the guide face. If, for example, you put a box in front of the",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "eyes of the guide face, a bar is placed in front of a detected person’s eyes in your",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "app’s ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.RealityKit/documentation/RealityKit/ARView",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ". For more details about ARKit face detection, see ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/ARKit/tracking-and-visualizing-faces",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "Face anchoring is only available when using the front-facing camera.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Note",
          "style": "note",
          "type": "aside"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "identifier": "selecting-an-anchor-for-a-reality-composer-scene-5",
              "type": "image"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Select-object-anchoring-to-place-a-scene-near-detected-objects",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Select object anchoring to place a scene near detected objects",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Select this anchor type to place your scene near a real-world object that ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/ARKit",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "has detected, based on an object that you’ve scanned. ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.RealityKit/documentation/RealityKit",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " automatically",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "detects objects matching your scan, and anchors your scene to it. Object anchoring",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "is a good choice for adding content to a real-world object like a toy, tool, or other",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "physical object. For more details about ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/ARKit",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "object detection, see ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/ARKit/scanning-and-detecting-3d-objects",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "identifier": "selecting-an-anchor-for-a-reality-composer-scene-6",
              "type": "image"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "After you select object anchoring, ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "Reality Composer",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text": " displays a yellow cube with",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "a red exclamation point inside. The cube represents the object your scene is anchored",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "to, and the exclamation point indicates that you need to identify the type of detected",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "object to anchor your scene to. In the Properties inspector, below the anchor type,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "select a scanned object asset to use as an anchor. An image of the scanned object",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "then replaces the exclamation point.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Unlike RealityKit image anchoring, object anchoring does not continuously track detected",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "objects. If a detected object moves, it may take a few seconds before the scene’s",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "position is updated to reflect its anchor’s new location.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "identifier": "selecting-an-anchor-for-a-reality-composer-scene-7",
              "type": "image"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Change-the-selected-anchor-type",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Change the selected anchor type",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "While building your scene, you may realize that a different anchor type is a better",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "fit for what you’re building. With ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "Reality Composer",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text": ", you can change the anchor",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "type of your scene at any time. Simply click or tap your scene’s background to deselect",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "any selected objects. Then check the Scene inspector for a section titled Anchor,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "which shows the five possible anchor types. Click the new anchor type you that want",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "to use for your scene.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "identifier": "selecting-an-anchor-for-a-reality-composer-scene-8",
              "type": "image"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "When you select a new anchor, none of your scene’s content changes, but the guides",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "are updated to reflect the new anchor type. You may have to adjust the location of",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "some of your objects to ensure that they still align correctly with the new guides.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
